FORMAT: 1A
HOST: http://127.0.0.1:5002/api

# Users API

A simple CRUD API for managing users, demonstrating API Blueprint.

## Users Collection [/users]

### List All Users [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
            {
                "id": 1,
                "name": "Alice Smith",
                "email": "alice@example.com"
            },
            {
                "id": 2,
                "name": "Bob Jones",
                "email": "bob@example.com"
            }
        ]

### Create a New User [POST]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "name": "Charlie Brown",
            "email": "charlie@example.com"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
            "id": 3,
            "name": "Charlie Brown",
            "email": "charlie@example.com"
        }

## User [/users/{user_id}]

+ Parameters
    + user_id: 1 (number, required) - The unique identifier of the user.

### Retrieve a User [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "id": 1,
            "name": "Alice Smith",
            "email": "alice@example.com"
        }

+ Response 404 (application/json)

        {
            "error": "User not found"
        }

### Update a User [PUT]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "name": "Alice Cooper",
            "email": "alice.cooper@example.com"
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "id": 1,
            "name": "Alice Cooper",
            "email": "alice.cooper@example.com"
        }

+ Response 404 (application/json)

        {
            "error": "User not found"
        }

### Delete a User [DELETE]

+ Response 204

+ Response 404 (application/json)

        {
            "error": "User not found"
        }
